#HTML
<!DOCTYPE html> - Tells browser this is HTML5
<html> - Root of the web page
<head> - Page information (title, meta, links)
<title> - Title shown on browser tab
<body> - Visible content of the page

<h1> - Main heading
<h2> - Sub heading
<h3> - Smaller heading

<p> - Paragraph
<span> - Style or target small part of text (inline)

<img> - Image (self-closing tag, uses src, alt, width, height)

<a href=""> - Link to another page/website
<button> - Clickable button
onclick - JavaScript action on button click

<br> - Line break (self-closing)
<hr> - Draws a horizontal line

<strong> - Bold text (important)
<em> - Italic text (emphasis)

<ul> - Unordered list (bullets)
<ol> - Ordered list (numbers)
<li> - List item (used inside ul/ol)

<audio> - Adds audio to webpage
<source> - Audio/video file source
controls - Shows play, pause, volume

<video> - Adds video to webpage
width / height - Size of video

<header> - Top section of website (logo/title)
<nav> - Navigation menu (links)
<footer> - Bottom section (copyright/info)
<table> - Create table
<tr> - Table row
<th> - Table heading
<td>- table data
<form> - Creates a form to collect user input

<input type="text"> - Text input field
<input type="password"> - Password input (hidden text)
<input type="email"> - Email input with validation
placeholder - Shows hint text inside input box

<label> - Label for input/textarea
for - Connects label with input/textarea id

<textarea> - Multi-line text input box
rows - Height of textarea
cols - Width of textarea

<select> - Dropdown list
<option> - Items inside dropdown

value - Data sent when option is select
#CSS - Makes website beautiful i.e, we can change colour, shape, position, size, design
who{
    what : how;
}
h1{
    color : red;
}
CSS 3 types:
1. Inline CSS - <h1 style = "color:red;">Hello</h1>
2. Internal CSS -
<style>
h1 {color:red;}
</style>
3. External CSS -
<link rel = "stylesheet" href ="style.css>"
